film/2020/feb/24/harvey-weinstein-guilty-trial-charges-verdict |website=The Guardian|publisher=The Guardian |date=February 24, 2020|accessdate=February 24, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[February 25]] &ndash; Amazon opens its first [[Amazon Go|cashierless grocery store]], located in [[Seattle]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Amazon opens its first cashierless grocery store|url=https://techcrunch.com/2020/02/25/amazon-opens-its-first-cashierless-grocery-store/|publisher=Tech Crunch |date=February 25, 2020|accessdate=February 26, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[February 27]]\n**COVID-19 pandemic: Growing fear of the COVID-19 coronavirus pandemic causes the [[Dow Jones Industrial Average]] to plunge by 1,190.95 points (4.4%), closing at 25,766.64\u2014its largest one-day points decline in history. This follows several days of large falls, the Dow's worst week since 2008.<ref>{{cite web |title=Dow plunges 1,100 points as the coronavirus sends the market tumbling into correction territory|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/02/26/dow-futures-fall-after-microsoft-issues-coronavirus-warning.html|publisher=CNBC |date=February 27, 2020|accessdate=February 27, 2020}}</ref>\n**Marine commandant General [[David H. Berger]] orders the removal of [[Confederate States of America|Confederate]] symbols from [[United States Marine Corps|Marine Corps]] bases around the world.<ref>[https://thehill.com/policy/defense/484897-marine-commandant-orders-removal-of-confederate-paraphernalia-at-bases Marine commandant orders removal of Confederate paraphernalia at bases] By Justin Wise, The Hill, February 27, 2020</ref>\n**Former [[Mayor of Baltimore|Baltimore mayor]] [[Catherine Pugh]] is sentenced to three years in prison and three years probation after pleading guilty to tax evasion and conspiracy to defraud the government.<ref>[https://baltimore.cbslocal.com/2020/02/27/catherine-pugh-healthy-holly-former-baltimore-mayor-sentenced-3-years-latest/ Catherine Pugh Sentenced To 3 Years In Prison In \u2018Healthy Holly\u2019 Scandal \u2013 CBS Baltimore<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n*[[February 29]]\n**The [[Presidency of Donald Trump|Trump administration]] and the [[Taliban]] sign a [[Afghan peace process#2020 agreement|conditional peace agreement]] in [[Doha]], [[Qatar]] as part of a process to end the [[War in Afghanistan (2001\u2013present)|war in Afghanistan]].<ref>[https://www.msn.com/en-ca/news/world/us-taliban-sign-landmark-agreement-in-bid-to-end-americas-longest-war/ar-BB10yMNg?ocid=sf2 U.S.-Taliban sign landmark agreement in bid to end America's longest war] NBC News, February 29, 2020</ref>\n**COVID-19 pandemic: The [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States#February|first death]] from COVID-19 in the U.S. is reported by [[Washington (state)|Washington State]] officials, as the total number of cases nationwide reaches 66.<ref>{{cite web |title=First coronavirus death in the U.S. happens in Washington state|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/1st-coronavirus-death-u-s-officials-say-n1145931|publisher=NBC News|date=February 29, 2020|accessdate=February 29, 2020}}</ref>\n**The [[2020 South Carolina Democratic primary]] is held;<ref>[https://thehill.com/homenews/campaign/485317-sanders-congratulates-biden-on-south-carolina-win-shifts-focus-to-super Sanders congratulates Biden on South Carolina win, shifts focus to Super Tuesday] BY JULIA MANCHESTER, The Hill, February 29, 2020</ref> billionaire candidate [[Tom Steyer]] suspends his presidential campaign.<ref>[https://thehill.com/homenews/campaign/485321-steyer-drops-out-of-2020-race Steyer drops out of 2020 race] The Hill, February 29, 2020</ref>\n\n=== March ===\n* [[March 1]] &ndash; Former [[South Bend, Indiana]] mayor [[Pete Buttigieg]] suspends his [[Pete Buttigieg 2020 presidential campaign|presidential campaign]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Buttigieg ends historic presidential campaign, urges unity|url=https://apnews.com/9a141437992adacfa6dfa04c4e197b86|publisher=AP|date=March 1, 2020|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref>\n* [