ews/2020/mar/13/donald-trump-coronavirus-national-emergency-sketch|title='I don't take responsibility': Trump shakes hands and spreads blame over coronavirus|website=The Guardian|date=March 14, 2020|access-date=March 14, 2020}}</ref>\n***The [[Food and Drug Administration]] (FDA) grants emergency authorization for a coronavirus test by Swiss diagnostics maker [[Hoffmann-La_Roche|Roche]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.roche.com/media/releases/med-cor-2020-03-13.htm|title=Roche's cobas SARS-CoV-2 Test to detect novel coronavirus receives FDA Emergency Use Authorization and is available in markets accepting the CE mark|date=March 13, 2020|access-date=March 13, 2020|work=Roche}}</ref>\n**[[Bill Gates]] steps down from the board of [[Microsoft]] to focus on philanthropic activities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-51883377|title=Bill Gates steps down from Microsoft board to focus on philanthropy|website=BBC News|date=March 13, 2020|access-date=March 14, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[March 15]] &ndash; COVID-19 pandemic: The [[Federal Reserve]] announces that it will cut its target interest rate to 0 to 0.25 percent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/pressreleases/monetary20200315a.htm|title=Federal Reserve issues FOMC statement|website=Federal Reserve|date=March 15, 2020|access-date=March 17, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[March 16]]\n**COVID-19 pandemic: \n***The Dow Jones [[2020 stock market crash#16\u201317 March|falls by \u22122,997.10]], the single [[List_of_largest_daily_changes_in_the_Dow_Jones_Industrial_Average|largest point drop in history]] and the second largest percentage drop ever at \u221212.93%, an even greater crash than the [[Wall Street Crash of 1929]].\n***The first Phase 1 clinical trial evaluating a potential COVID-19 vaccine begins at [[Kaiser_Permanente|Kaiser Permanente Washington Health Research Institute]] in [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Washington (state)|Seattle]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nih.gov/news-events