 death in the U.S. happens in Washington state|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/1st-coronavirus-death-u-s-officials-say-n1145931|publisher=NBC News|date=February 29, 2020|accessdate=February 29, 2020}}</ref>\n**The [[2020 South Carolina Democratic primary]] is held;<ref>[https://thehill.com/homenews/campaign/485317-sanders-congratulates-biden-on-south-carolina-win-shifts-focus-to-super Sanders congratulates Biden on South Carolina win, shifts focus to Super Tuesday] BY JULIA MANCHESTER, The Hill, February 29, 2020</ref> billionaire candidate [[Tom Steyer]] suspends his presidential campaign.<ref>[https://thehill.com/homenews/campaign/485321-steyer-drops-out-of-2020-race Steyer drops out of 2020 race] The Hill, February 29, 2020</ref>\n\n=== March ===\n* [[March 1]] &ndash; Former [[South Bend, Indiana]] mayor [[Pete Buttigieg]] suspends his [[Pete Buttigieg 2020 presidential campaign|presidential campaign]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Buttigieg ends historic presidential campaign, urges unity|url=https://apnews.com/9a141437992adacfa6dfa04c4e197b86|publisher=AP|date=March 1, 2020|accessdate=March 2, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[March 2]]\n**A [[Tornado outbreak of March 2\u20133, 2020|tornado outbreak]] strikes four counties around [[Nashville, Tennessee]], killing 26 people.<ref>[https://www.today.com/video/nashville-tornado-death-toll-rises-to-at-least-24-dozens-still-missing-79981637617?cid=sm_npd_td_fb_ma&fbclid=IwAR0WYx_MD4TnQ_bHQo_Tv9_kOlvq4lo9bxdUjYCPBmeuu6OZ_R_tIeutm1U Nashville tornado death toll rises to at least 24; dozens still missing] Today (NBC News), March 4, 2020  [https://www.cbsnews.com/news/nashville-tornado-putnam-county-death-toll-rises-today-2020-04-03/ Tennessee couple describes \"flying in the air\" during deadly tornado] By DAVID BEGNAUD, CBS NEWS, March 4, 2020</ref>\n**Senator [[Amy Klobuchar]] suspends her [[Amy Klobuchar 2020 presidential campaign|presidential campaign]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Corasaniti|first=Nick|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/02/us/politics/amy-klobuchar-drops-out.html|title=Amy Klobuchar Drops Out of Presidential Race and Plans to Endorse Biden|date=March 2, 2020|work=The New York Times|access-date=March 2, 2020|last2=Burns|first2=Alexander|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n**[[MSNBC]] commentator [[Chris Matthews]] (''[[Hardball with Chris Matthews]]'') announces his retirement.<ref>[https://www.nbcnews.com/news/all/chris-matthews-announces-retirement-mutually-parts-ways-msnbc-n1147536?cid=sm_npd_nn_fb_ma&fbclid=IwAR1_nA67J_YjfyBpNVLPrTrH4r0lQz1PZZEz8Cl76zBGAdhKsm7_VSKvZCI Chris Matthews announces retirement, mutually parts ways with MSNBC] By Jason Abbruzzese, NBC News, March 2, 2020</ref>\n* [[March 3]] &ndash; [[Super Tuesday#2020|Super Tuesday 2020]]<ref>[https://www.uspresidentialelectionnews.com/2020-presidential-primary-schedule-calendar/super-tuesday-2020/ Super Tuesday 2020] Election Central, retrieved December 22, 2019</ref>\n* March 3&ndash;[[March 10|10]] &ndash; [[2020 Democrats Abroad primary]]<ref name=politics/> Bernie Sanders 23,139 votes (57.9%), 9 delegates; Joe Biden 9,059 votes (22.7%), 4 delegates<ref>[https://www.democratsabroad.org/2020_gpp_results The 2020 Global Presidential Primary Results Are In!] posted by DA NEWS, DA NEWS EDITOR, 23 March 2020</ref>\n* [[March 4]]\n**[[COVID-19]] pandemic: At least 130 cases of COVID-19 are reported in the United States, with ten deaths in [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Washington (state)|Washington State]] and one in [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in California|California]].<ref>[https://www.cbsnews.com/live-updates/coronavirus-outbreak-death-toll-us-infections-latest-news-updates-2020-03-04/ Coronavirus updates: U.S. death toll rises to 11 with California's first death] CBS News, March 4, 2020</ref> California governor [[Gavin Newsom]] declares a state of emergency.<ref>[https://thehill.com/policy/healthcare/486046-california-governor-declares-state-of-emergency-over-coronavirus?fbclid=IwAR0kcfjo8IH0m5fP9Fgm0_Srig